<i><b><h2>How to Reach Siena</h2></b></i>
<h3><i>It is possible to reach Siena by car,
by bus or by train. In Siena there is no airport, the closest ones are in
Florence at Peretola (Amerigo Vespucci Airport, 90 Km.) and in Pisa (Galileo
Galilei Airport, 130 Km.).
<ul>
   <li> <font color=blue>By car</font> <br>
        Siena is 57 Km. south of the A1 motorway exit "Firenze Certosa"
(coming from north) and 32 Km. west of the A1 motorway exit "Valdichiana
Bettolle - Sinalunga" (coming from south)
     <li><font color=blue>By bus</font><br>
          Bus lines in Siena are from or to Florence, from or to Rome , from
or to Grosseto and from or to Arezzo.  For further information about the bus
schedules visit the web page of <a href="http://www.lazzi.it/senaautolinee/">
public transport company</a>

      <li><font color=blue> By train</font><br>
           Visit the website of the <a href="http://www.trenitalia.it">
Italian railways</a> and choose your itinerary. The average duration of
journeys are respectively: Florence Santa Maria Novella 1h55min (change in
Empoli), Pisa Centrale 2h15min (change in Empoli), Roma Termini 3h20min
(change in Chiusi)

      <li> <font color=blue>Arriving at Pisa airport</font><br>
           There is a railway station inside Galilieo Galilei Airport
           through which you reach Pisa Central Station in 5 minutes. From
           there you can take the train to Siena. It is also possible to book
           a taxi, the average duration of the car journey from the gate
           to Siena downtown is about 1h20min, the cost is about 130 Euros
           + taxes

        <li> <font color=blue>Arriving at Florence airport (Amerigo Vespucci
             Airport)</font><br>
             You can reach Florence downtown in 20 minutes with the Sita/Ataf
             Service "Vola in Bus", 66 buses per day that every 30 minutes
             link the Amerigo Vespucci Airport to Santa Maria Novella Railways
             Station. From there you can take both the train or the bus to
             Siena. From the airport, it is also possible to book a taxi, the
             average duration of the car journey from the gate to Siena
             downtown is about  1h10min, and the cost is about 100
             Euros + taxes

     <li><font color=blue>Arriving at Rome airport (Leonardo Da Vinci,
          Fiumicino)</font><br> From the airport, you can reach Roma Termini
          railway station where you can take a train to Siena, or
          Roma Tiburtina railway station where you can take a bus to Siena.
          It is also possible to book a taxi from the airport. The average
          duration of the car journey
          from the Leonardo Da Vinci Airport to Siena downtown is about
          2h45min, and the cost is about 280 Euros + taxes
</h3>
